==Preseason== The Buffaloes are in their final season in the Big 12, as they will be moving to the [[Pac-12]] in 2011â12.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.big12sports.com/ViewArticle.dbml?&ATCLID=204998596&DB_OEM_ID=10410 |title=Terms for Colorado Withdrawal From Big 12 Announced |work=[[Big 12 Conference]] |accessdate=September 21, 2010}}</ref> They finished the previous season with a record of 15â16 and 6â10 in Big 12 Conference play. Of those 16 losses, seven were by six points or less. Additionally, all five starters return from that team.<ref name=king/>
In the Big 12 preseason coaches' poll, the Buffaloes were picked to finish ninth. [[Cory Higgins]] was named the Preseason All-Conference First Team, while [[Alec Burks]] was an honorable mention.<ref name=longmont>{{cite news|first=Brian|last=Howell|url=http://www.timescall.com/sports_story.asp?id=23873|title=CU sets out to exceed expectations |accessdate=January 11, 2011|date=October 16, 2010|work=[[Longmont Times-Call]]}}</ref> Both were also named to the 50-man preseason [[Wooden Award]] watchlist.<ref name=wooden>{{cite web|url=http://www.woodenaward.com/?p=861|title=2010â2011 Menâs Preseason Top 50 List|work=[[John R. Wooden Award]]|accessdate=November 12, 2010}}</ref> Additionally, Burks was on the 50-man preseason [[Naismith College Player of the Year]] watchlist.<ref name=naismith>{{cite web|url=http://www.shupirates.com//pdf8/723283.pdf|title=Duke University Leads a Diverse Pack on the Naismith Preseason Watchlist|work=MSL Atlanta|accessdate=November 16, 2010}}</ref> [[Gary Parrish]] picked them eighth in the Big 12, and said that he "won't be shocked if they ride the Higgins-Burks tandem into the top half of the league and make the NCAA tournament for the first time since 2003."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbssports.com/collegebasketball/story/14241463/big-12-preview-competition-could-breed-national-contender|title=Big 12 preview: Competition could breed national contender|first=Gary|last=Parrish|work=[[CBS Sports]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|date=November 4, 2010|accessdate=January 12, 2011}}</ref> Jason King of [[Rivals.com]] named the Buffaloes the sixth-best team in conference, adding, "Don't be surprised if long-suffering Colorado sneaks into the NCAA tournament."<ref name=king>{{cite web|url=http://collegebasketball.rivals.com/content.asp?CID=1145850|title=League preview: Big 12|first=Jason|last=King|work=[[Rivals.com]]|publisher=[[Yahoo! Sports]]|date=October 31, 2010|accessdate=January 12, 2011}}</ref>
