==Season== ===Preconference season=== The Buffaloes defeated in-state rivals [[Colorado State]] 93â80 in overtime, behind [[Alec Burks]]' 25 points. Marcus Relphorde contributed 18 points and Cory Higgins added 15. Levi Knutson hit four free throws in the final 57 seconds to seal the victory.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://espn.go.com/ncb/recap?gameId=303420038|title=Colorado 90, Colorado St. 83|agency=[[Associated Press]]|work=[[ESPN]]|publisher=ESPN Internet Ventures|date=December 8, 2010|accessdate=January 12, 2011}}</ref>
===Big 12 season=== Snapping a losing streak of 13 consecutive conference openers, Colorado knocked off #8 [[2010â11 Missouri Tigers men's basketball team|Missouri]] 89â76 as [[Alec Burks]] exploded for a career-high 36 points. This was the Buffaloes' first win over a top ten team since defeating #3 [[Texas Longhorns men's basketball|Texas]] in 2003. [[Cory Higgins]] had 18 points and a career-tying 10 rebounds. The Buffaloes had a 12-point halftime lead and never let Missouri get closer than seven in the second half.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://espn.go.com/ncb/recap?gameId=310080038|title=Colorado star Alec Burks scores 36, helps hand No. 8 Missouri a second loss|agency=[[Associated Press]]|work=[[ESPN]]|publisher=ESPN Internet Ventures|date=January 8, 2011|accessdate=January 14, 2011}}</ref>
===Post-season=== The Buffs have been selected as the #1 seed for the 2011 NIT Tournament
